<p>A: For adult smokers seeking to switch, RELX can be a good alternative. It delivers nicotine in a potentially less harmful way than cigarettes and eliminates many of the harmful chemicals associated with burning tobacco. However, it's not risk-free and contains nicotine, an addictive substance.</p>

<p><strong>Q: How long does a RELX pod typically last?</strong></p>

<p>A:  A RELX pod's lifespan depends on individual usage habits.  For an average user, a pod can last anywhere from 1-3 days. Pod capacity and vaping frequency are the main factors.</p>

<p><strong>Q:  Are RELX vapes safe?</strong></p>

<p>A: While considered less harmful than traditional cigarettes, RELX vapes are not entirely safe.  They contain nicotine, which is addictive and has potential health effects.  Vaping in general carries some risks, and long-term health effects are still being studied.  RELX is intended for adult smokers seeking a harm-reduction option, not for non-smokers or youth.</p>

